definitions.definition: A group of geese when they are on the ground or on the water.
Any group or gathering of related things, particularly one perceived as noisy , boisterous or chaotic .
Short for press gaggle : an informal briefing of journalists.

main_definition: ( collective ) A group of geese when they are on the ground or on the water.
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) Any group or gathering of related things, particularly one perceived as noisy , boisterous or chaotic .
Short for press gaggle : an informal briefing of journalists.
